      <description>&lt;p&gt;I am heading the economics and financial markets research team at the &lt;!-- raw HTML omitted --&gt;German Insurance Association&lt;!-- raw HTML omitted --&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previously, I held posts at the Department for Forecasting and Economic Policy at the German Institute for Economic Research (DIW) in Berlin, the French Conseil d&amp;rsquo;Analyse Economique in Paris, and the Hertie School where in 2021 I completed a PhD in economics. I (co-)authored many policy reports, notably for the European Parliament and at the DIW, and participated in the so-called &amp;ldquo;Joint Economic Forecast&amp;rdquo; of the leading German economic research institutes. I also taught courses in macroeconomics, international trade, and economic policy at universities in France, Germany, and the US.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My academic research focuses on the intersection of the real and financial sector, in particular financial regulation and business cycle synchronization in the Eurozone.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
